<subSubSection id="9CEBECA8A817F111FF5EFED7FBFA9824" box="[178,1033,299,321]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="D44EBF23A817F111FF5EFED7FBFA9824" blockId="6.[178,1033,299,321]" box="[178,1033,299,321]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">Etymology: The species name refers to the known distribution of the species.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9CEBECA8A817F111FF5EFEACFE8D9D52" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367" type="description">
<paragraph id="D44EBF23A817F111FF5EFEACFE2698E6" blockId="6.[178,1085,336,387]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">
Description: General appearance as figured (
<figureCitation id="4CCAA3A6A817F111FD0DFEACFCD79800" box="[737,804,336,358]" captionStart="Figs 7-9" captionStartId="19.[178,218,1505,1527]" captionTargetBox="[178,1086,212,1573]" captionTargetId="figure-0@19.[178,1085,212,1573]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figs 7-9: Anthracus philippinensis nov.sp. Habitus, head and pronotum. (7) PT, Philippines, Panay, E Bontol, (8) HT, (9) PT, Philippines, Mindoro, E Puerto Galera, Sabang." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5193665" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5193665/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Body length 
<quantity id="130912C6A817F111FC28FEACFBCE9800" box="[964,1085,336,357]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.45" metricValueMax="3.7" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367" unit="mm" value="3.45" valueMax="3.7" valueMin="3.2">3.2-3.7 mm</quantity>
(HT 3.4); width 
<quantity id="130912C6A817F111FEB4FE91FE2398E6" box="[344,464,365,387]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367" unit="mm" value="1.4" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.3">1.3-1.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D44EBF23A817F111FF5EFE6FFD4D9BF6" blockId="6.[178,1085,403,659]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">
Shiny, pronotum weakly, elytra moderately iridescent. Colour of upper surface usually paler than in 
<taxonomicName id="13F1C4A0A817F111FEA8FE4CFE2298A0" baseAuthorityName="ANDREWES" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[324,465,432,453]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anthracus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nesophilus">
<emphasis id="E6856331A817F111FEA8FE4CFE2298A0" box="[324,465,432,453]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">A. nesophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with head and pronotum reddish yellow, but clypeus and labrum paler, and mandibles with inner margins and apices blackish. Rarely, the pronotal disc is weakly infuscated leaving all margins widely reddish yellow. Elytra reddish yellow, with each elytron having a large dark brown central macula, expanding laterally to interval 8 and leaving basal and lateral quarter and first interval reddish yellow. Legs, palpi and first two antennomeres pale yellowish brown, antennomeres 3-11 moderately infuscated. Ventral surface mainly reddish brown, prosternum and epipleura somewhat paler, and pro- and metepisterna weakly infuscated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D44EBF23A817F111FF5EFD5EFCE19BB0" blockId="6.[178,1085,674,725]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">
Head, pronotum (
<figureCitation id="4CCAA3A6A817F111FE81FD5EFE359BDD" box="[365,454,674,696]" captionStart="Figs 7-9" captionStartId="19.[178,218,1505,1527]" captionTargetBox="[178,1086,212,1573]" captionTargetId="figure-0@19.[178,1085,212,1573]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figs 7-9: Anthracus philippinensis nov.sp. Habitus, head and pronotum. (7) PT, Philippines, Panay, E Bontol, (8) HT, (9) PT, Philippines, Mindoro, E Puerto Galera, Sabang." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5193665" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5193665/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">Figs 7-9</figureCitation>
) and elytra (
<figureCitation id="4CCAA3A6A817F111FDB9FD5EFD659BDD" box="[597,662,674,696]" captionStart="Figs 7-9" captionStartId="19.[178,218,1505,1527]" captionTargetBox="[178,1086,212,1573]" captionTargetId="figure-0@19.[178,1085,212,1573]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figs 7-9: Anthracus philippinensis nov.sp. Habitus, head and pronotum. (7) PT, Philippines, Panay, E Bontol, (8) HT, (9) PT, Philippines, Mindoro, E Puerto Galera, Sabang." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5193665" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5193665/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) very similar to those of the preceding species with no specific differences in shape or proportions.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D44EBF23A817F111FF5EFD19FD699A50" blockId="6.[178,1085,741,821]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">
Microsculpture of upper surface similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="13F1C4A0A817F111FD51FD19FCB49B9F" baseAuthorityName="ANDREWES" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[701,839,741,762]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anthracus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nesophilus">
<emphasis id="E6856331A817F111FD51FD19FCB49B9F" box="[701,839,741,762]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">A. nesophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the microsculpture on the frons and anterior half of vertex sometimes almost lacking and on pronotal surface usually less distinct and more lightly impressed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D44EBF23A817F111FF5EFCB8FE099AD7" blockId="6.[178,1086,836,946]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">Metepisterna long and narrowed posteriad, at inner margin about 1.6 times longer than wide at basal margin. Prosternum medially with 5-6 and in front of apical margin with 8 medium long setae (often broken and then insertion points difficult to observe). Prosternal process with 2 distinct setae.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D44EBF23A817F111FF5EFC3EFD139AB2" blockId="6.[178,736,962,984]" box="[178,736,962,984]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">
Protarsomeres and mesotarsomeres as in 
<taxonomicName id="13F1C4A0A817F111FDBEFC3EFD299AB2" baseAuthorityName="ANDREWES" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[594,730,962,983]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anthracus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nesophilus">
<emphasis id="E6856331A817F111FDBEFC3EFD299AB2" box="[594,730,962,983]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">A. nesophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D44EBF23A817F111FF5EFC1BFE8D9D52" blockId="6.[178,1085,999,1079]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">
Median lobe of aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="4CCAA3A6A817F111FE38FC1BFDBB9A98" box="[468,584,999,1021]" captionStart="Figs 35-41" captionStartId="27.[178,218,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[150,1112,197,1640]" captionTargetId="figure-0@27.[150,1112,197,1640]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figs 35-41: Anthracus philippinensis nov.sp. Median lobe of aedoeagus, lateral and dorsal aspect. (35, 38) PT, Philippines, Mindoro, E Puerto Galera, (36, 40) PT, Philippines, Panay, E Bontol, (37, 39) PT, Philippines, Luzon, Los Banos." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5194866" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5194866/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">Figs 35-41</figureCitation>
) similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="13F1C4A0A817F111FCCCFC1BFC5D9A99" baseAuthorityName="ANDREWES" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[800,942,999,1020]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anthracus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nesophilus">
<emphasis id="E6856331A817F111FCCCFC1BFC5D9A99" box="[800,942,999,1020]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">A. nesophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but smaller, somewhat more arcuate ventrad, and internal sac with 3-5 larger, more closely arranged teeth in central part.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9CEBECA8A817F111FF5EFBBBFCB19CE4" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D44EBF23A817F111FF5EFBBBFCB19CE4" blockId="6.[178,1086,1095,1409]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">
Comparisons and remarks: 
<taxonomicName id="13F1C4A0A817F111FD6DFBBBFC8E9D39" authority="Jaeger, 2015" authorityName="Jaeger" authorityYear="2015" box="[641,893,1095,1116]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anthracus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philippinensis" status="nov.sp.">
<emphasis id="E6856331A817F111FD6DFBBBFC8E9D39" box="[641,893,1095,1116]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">Anthracus philippinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="FDB6DE4AA817F111FC6FFBBBFC3E9D39" box="[899,973,1095,1116]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367" rank="species">nov.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is the only species of the 
<taxonomicName id="13F1C4A0A817F111FEA8FB98FDD99D1F" box="[324,554,1124,1146]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anthracus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annamensis">
<emphasis id="E6856331A817F111FEA8FB98FDD99D1F" box="[324,554,1124,1146]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">Anthracus annamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group so far known from the 
<collectingCountry id="ACE6FFB3A817F111FCB0FB98FC3D9D1F" box="[860,974,1124,1146]" name="Philippines" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">Philippines</collectingCountry>
and represents a closely related vicariant of 
<taxonomicName id="13F1C4A0A817F111FDF3FB7EFD599DF3" baseAuthorityName="ANDREWES" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[543,682,1153,1175]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anthracus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nesophilus">
<emphasis id="E6856331A817F111FDF3FB7EFD599DF3" box="[543,682,1153,1175]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">A. nesophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Java, Sulawesi and Sumbawa. It differs from the latter species by the absolutely smaller, ventrally more clearly curved median lobe of the aedeagus and its internal structures with a group of 3-5 larger, more closely and more centrally arranged teeth (see 
<figureCitation id="4CCAA3A6A817F111FD61FB25FD089D8A" box="[653,763,1241,1263]" captionStart="Figs 35-41" captionStartId="27.[178,218,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[150,1112,197,1640]" captionTargetId="figure-0@27.[150,1112,197,1640]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figs 35-41: Anthracus philippinensis nov.sp. Median lobe of aedoeagus, lateral and dorsal aspect. (35, 38) PT, Philippines, Mindoro, E Puerto Galera, (36, 40) PT, Philippines, Panay, E Bontol, (37, 39) PT, Philippines, Luzon, Los Banos." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5194866" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5194866/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">Figs 35-41</figureCitation>
respectively 24-34). Externally both species are very similar and show no significant differences in shape of head, pronotum or elytra. However, in 
<taxonomicName id="13F1C4A0A817F111FDE2FAE8FD499C4C" authorityName="Jaeger" authorityYear="2015" box="[526,698,1300,1321]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anthracus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philippinensis">
<emphasis id="E6856331A817F111FDE2FAE8FD499C4C" box="[526,698,1300,1321]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">A. philippinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the pronotum is usually reddish yellow, instead of dark reddish or blackish brown as in 
<emphasis id="E6856331A817F111FD34FACDFC9A9C23" box="[728,873,1329,1350]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">
<taxonomicName id="13F1C4A0A817F111FD34FACDFC969C23" baseAuthorityName="ANDREWES" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[728,869,1329,1350]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anthracus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nesophilus">A. nesophilus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and the microsculpture on pronotal disc is often less distinctly impressed, but atypical specimens of both taxa show no significant differences in colour or microsculpture.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9CEBECA8A817F111FF5EFA6DFD699CA1" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="D44EBF23A817F111FF5EFA6DFD699CA1" blockId="6.[178,1085,1425,1476]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">
Distribution 
<taxonomicName id="13F1C4A0A817F111FE71FA6DFDB99CC3" authorityName="Jaeger" authorityYear="2015" box="[413,586,1425,1446]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anthracus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philippinensis">
<emphasis id="E6856331A817F111FE71FA6DFDB99CC3" box="[413,586,1425,1446]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">A. philippinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is so far known from the 
<collectingCountry id="ACE6FFB3A817F111FC89FA6DFBEC9CC2" box="[869,1055,1425,1447]" name="Philippines" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">Philippine Islands</collectingCountry>
of Luzon, Mindoro, Mindanao and Panay (
<figureCitation id="4CCAA3A6A817F111FDA4FA52FD7C9CA1" box="[584,655,1454,1476]" captionStart="Fig 80" captionStartId="34.[178,210,909,931]" captionTargetBox="[266,997,212,896]" captionTargetId="figure-65@34.[266,997,212,896]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="Fig 80: Distribution: A. nesophilus (ANDREWES) (triangles), A. javaensis nov.sp. (white star), A. sumatraensis nov.sp. (square) A. philippinensis nov.sp. (circle), A. siamensis nov.sp. (black star)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5193681" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5193681/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="1367">Fig 80</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
